description:
Located on a quiet street in the family friendly area of Braitling only a short distance from primary school, local shops and sporting oval. This spacious four Bedroom, two bathroom home also has two separate living areas, one of which could be utilised as a fifth bedroom for the growing family or simply left as a living retreat.

This home features:
- Central open plan living, dining and kitchen surrounded by the lounge and 4 bedrooms
- Tiled throughout for easy cleaning and maintenance
- 4 Bedrooms and 2 Bathrooms
- Main bedroom has robes and ensuite
- Large 1000 m parcel of land
- Plenty of room for parking at the front, side and rear of the property including a carport
- Ducted evaporative cooling and split system air conditioners.
- Solar hot water

Entering this tidy home, you will immediately appreciate the generous kitchen with large gas top oven, stacks of storage, pantry space and an island bench with breakfast bar to enjoy family focussed cooking time. The open plan kitchen looks over the dining area which opens into lounge space currently utilised as a games area.

Wrapped around the main living area are the four bedrooms and a separate lounge area. The main room has built in robes and an ensuite whilst the second main room features a clever walk-through robe that also has ample room for a study area. The third room has a built-in wardrobe and the fourth is spacious enough for a double bed and stand-alone storage.

The lounge room is bright and spacious and looks out over the covered outdoor area. In the large, fully fenced back yard is a sizeable, powered shed and a brick BBQ. The rest of the garden space offers a mass of potential for those wanting to landscape or drop in a pool.

This home is sure to catch the eye of those looking for a solid family home that offers an abundance of space inside and out.

Call to make a time to view this property today!

Council Rates: $2,234.30 p.a.
Currently rented for $620 per week
